%N A394235 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of equivalence classes of trees with n nodes whose labels cover [k], under the adjacency monomial E.
%C A394235 Here a tree T has an associated adjacency monomial E = x_1^(k_1) * x_2^(k_2) * x_3^(k_3) * ... with k_i being the number of pairs of vertices of T that have the same label and are separated by i edges. Two trees are then considered equivalent if they have the same monomial E.
%H A394235 John Tyler Rascoe, <a href="/A394235/a394235.py.txt">Python code</a>.
%e A394235 Triangle begins:
%e A394235      k=0   1    2     3    4    5   6  7  8
%e A394235   n=0 [1]
